<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:lang="en" xml:id="ishermitian">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>ishermitian</refname>
        <refpurpose>Check whether a matrix is hermitian</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>
            t = ishermitian(A)
        </synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection role="arguments">
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>A</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        real or complex square matrix.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>t</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        boolean value (%t or %f). Returns %t if the matrix is Hermitian, %f otherwise.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection role="description">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            <literal>ishermitian</literal> returns %t if the matrix <literal>A</literal> is hermitian, that is if <literal>A* = A</literal>, where 
            <literal>A*</literal> denotes the conjugate transpose of <literal>A</literal>.
        </para>
        <para>
            Equivalently, a matrix is hermitian if <literal>A(i,j) = conj(A(j,i))</literal> for all indices <literal>i</literal> and <literal>j</literal>. 
            And diagonal elements must be real.
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection role="example">
        <title>Examples</title>
        <para>
            <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
                X = [1 %i; -%i 2];
                ishermitian(X)
                // %t
            ]]></programlisting>
        </para>
        <para>
            <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
                X = [1 %i; %i 2];
                ishermitian(X)
                // %f
            ]]></programlisting>
        </para>
        <para>
            <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
                X = [1 2; 2 3];
                ishermitian(X)
                // %t
            ]]></programlisting>
        </para>
    </refsection>
